        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer2496488985&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2496488985" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9316074794012804520">I did enjoy a lot of this book. The interaction between Darcy and Elizabeth were usually quite entertaining. My problem with they story is how much the author strayed from the original story. I understand the author would have to use her own material for Darcy&apos;s thoughts and parts of the story through his perspective, but to totally rewrite the story line was ridiculous. Darcy going back to talk to Jane. Elizabeth never visiting Pemberley with her Aunt and Uncle. I&apos;m sorry but I didn&apos;t like that</span>
  <span id="freeText9316074794012804520" style="display:none">I did enjoy a lot of this book. The interaction between Darcy and Elizabeth were usually quite entertaining. My problem with they story is how much the author strayed from the original story. I understand the author would have to use her own material for Darcy's thoughts and parts of the story through his perspective, but to totally rewrite the story line was ridiculous. Darcy going back to talk to Jane. Elizabeth never visiting Pemberley with her Aunt and Uncle. I'm sorry but I didn't like that Mr. Darcy acted improperly through a lot of this book.</span>
